# SEE-Monitor .gitattributes
# Enforce LF line endings so shell scripts pushed from Windows don't arrive on
# the Linux server with CRLF (which breaks '#!/bin/bash' with a bad-interpreter
# error). Applies on checkout regardless of the client's core.autocrlf setting.

* text=auto eol=lf

*.sh   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.conf text eol=lf
*.service text eol=lf
*.target  text eol=lf
*.env  text eol=lf

# Binary-ish assets: leave untouched
*.db   binary
*.pem  binary
*.p12  binary
*.png  binary
*.zip  binary

# NOTE: .gitattributes cannot set the executable bit. To carry +x through Git
# (so scripts are runnable after a pull on Linux even when pushed from
# Windows), mark them once in the index and commit:
#
#   git update-index --chmod=+x install.sh \
#       scripts/fix-permissions.sh scripts/deploy.sh scripts/sync-tree.sh \
#       scripts/wait-for-db.sh scripts/reassess_all.py see_monitor.py
#   git commit -m "Mark scripts executable"
#
# After that, 'git pull' on the server restores +x automatically. As a
# belt-and-suspenders fallback, run scripts/fix-permissions.sh after deploys.
